Blume's formula is a method to get the best estimate average annual return based on the historic arithmetic and geometric returns. The formula is given as:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Return}&=\dfrac{\text{T}-1}{\text{N}-1} \times \text{Geometric average} + \dfrac{\text{N}-\text{T}}{\text{N}-1} \times \text{Arithmetic average}
\end{aligned}$$

Where

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{T}&=\text{number of years being estimated}\\
\text{N}&=\text{Number of historic years}
\end{aligned}$$
